  "title": "Pectoral Region",
  "body_html": "<div>Knowledge of the anatomy of the pectoral region is required as set out on page 1 of the CEM syllabus. This is limited to surface anatomy, innervation and action of the key muscles.<br /><br />Knowledge of the following muscles is required:<br /><br /><div class=\"table-responsive\"><table class = \"tlarge table table-striped table-bordered\"  data-role=\"table\" id=\"tableid1\" ><thead><tr><th>Muscle</th><th>Innervation</th><th>Nerve root origins</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Pectoralis Major</td><td>Medial & lateral pectoral nerve</td><td>C5 to T1</td></tr><tr><td>Pectoralis Minor</td><td>Medial pectoral nerve</td><td>C8 and T1</td></tr><tr><td>Trapezius</td><td>Accessory nerve & C3/C4</td><td>See innervation</td></tr><tr><td>Latissimus Dorsi</td><td>Thoracodorsal nerve</td><td>C6 to C8</td></tr><tr><td>Serratus Anterior</td><td>Long thoracic nerve</td><td>C5 to C7</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br /><i>Diagram illustrating position of Pectoralis Major muscle</i><br /><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb003b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb003.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pectoralis major'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb003b.png'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></CENTER><br /><i>Diagram illustrating position of Pectoralis Minor</i><br /><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.